pageContext.claim: “You're the one that takes all the money from Wall Street. I don't take it...You're the one who takes the money from Wall Street, not me.”
pageContext.analysis: Biden may have received more money but of course Trump receives campaign contributions from Wall Street firms. According to opensecrets.org, Trump’s campaign committee has received about $20 million from PACs. Super PACS and individuals working in the securities industry — the second highest total of any candidate for president.
